    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-16T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="510"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-17T13:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 17—6:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Department’s telegram 68 of June 29.<note n="72" xml:id="d510fn72">See
                        footnote 71, <ref target="#pg_734">p. 734</ref>.</note> American
                    Government’s proposal accepted by Japan. Formal approval to amended resolution
                    has been given by the Japanese Government on condition that the other
                    Governments which participated in the Washington Conference give similar
                    approval. It is the desire of the Japanese Government that as provided by the
                    fourth clause of the resolution the American Government invite other powers
                    which have treaty relations with China to adhere. It is the especial wish of the
                    Japanese Government that the adherence of Germany be invited as it is the
                    opinion of the Japanese Government that there will be a very close relation
                    between German participation and an effective execution of the resolution.</p>
                <p>Certified copy of Japanese note approving the resolution is being mailed.<note
                        n="73" xml:id="d510fn73">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
